               <head>Commentary on Maimonides' Mishneh Torah</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A commentary on parts of Maimonides' Mishneh Torah. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="273v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="en">Perush Mishneh Torah [Sefer ha-mada῾]</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">פרוש משנה תורה [ספר מדע]</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">῾Ala ud-Din al-Muwaḳḳit</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he">עלאי אל דין אלמווקת</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A Judeo-Arabic commentary on the first four chapters of Maimonides Sefer ha-mada῾, with various additions by redactor(s). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The commentary on the second chapter begins on folio 47r, on the third, folio 55r, on the fourth, folio 161v. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Maimonides' text appears in an Arabic form. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <msItem rend="v">
                        
                        
                        
                        <locus from="1r" to="72r"/>
                        
                        
                        
